To build raisim doc, you need the following python packages:

* sphinx
* sphinx-rtd-theme
* breathe
* sphinx-tabs
* docutils

Recommended (avoid system Python issues on Ubuntu/Debian):

  python3 -m venv .venv
  . .venv/bin/activate
  python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
  sphinx-build -b html . _build/html

The CMake docs build will prefer a local venv at `docs/.venv` if it exists.
If not found, it falls back to a system `sphinx-build`. If neither is
available, it stops with the same venv instructions above.

You can get the latest doc from raisim.com
